<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-12-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-12-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="685" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d685">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-12-17"><hi rend="italic">December 17,
                                    1895</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 721.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 695, of the 28th
                            ultimo, in regard to the protection of American missionaries in Turkey,
                            and cordially approve <pb facs="0669" n="1403" xml:id="pg_1403"/> your
                            note of November 27 to the minister of foreign affairs on the
                            subject.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>